    "author_association": "CONTRIBUTOR",
    "body": "I can't offer a diagnosis yet, but after experimenting I observed that a user's \"network state\" as displayed in another user's Members column in a community is often out of sync with the set state or actual state of the user:\r\n\r\nLet's say there are two users: User1 and User2.\r\n\r\nUser1 sets their state as online and is not idle: User2 over time sees User1 transition from online to idle to offline (any order, seems non-deterministic). Those transitions don't happen quickly (usually): you have to setup the experiments and interact and  keep an eye on them.\r\n\r\nSame thing when User1 sets their state as online and *is* idle.\r\n\r\nSame thing when User1 sets their state as offline and is or is not idle.\r\n\r\nRe: all the above, what User1 sees in their own Members column re: *their self* can likewise be out of sync.\r\n\r\nI intend to dig into the code, but clearly network state tracking is *completely out of whack* re: what's expected to be displayed in own and others' Members columns.",
